A Latin word meaning 'a small band'. Fascicularis is often used in scientific names. For example:

The [[Crab-eating Macaque]], ''Macaca fascicularis'';

The Narrow-Leaf [[Milkweed]], ''Asclepias fascicularis'';

The cactus ''Haageocereus fascicularis'';

The tree ''Henriettella fascicularis'';

The fish ''Serranus fascicularis'';

The Australian plant ''Darwinia fascicularis''.

